<item>
            <title>[DERBY-21] ResultsetMetaData.getColumnClassName() for CLOB and BLOB datatypes is incorrect.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-21</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Opening this bug on behalf of Daniel Debrunner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
ResultsetMetaData.getColumnClassName() for CLOB and BLOB &lt;br/&gt;
datatypes is incorrect. &lt;br/&gt;
            BLOB:               CLOB:&lt;br/&gt;
jcc:        java.sql.Blob       java.sql.Clob&lt;br/&gt;
Derby:      byte[]              java.lang.String&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Derby&apos;s embedded JDBC driver returns the incorrect class &lt;br/&gt;
names for BLOB and CLOB columns in a ResultSet when using the &lt;br/&gt;
ResultSetMetaData.getColumnClassName() method. Note that the &lt;br/&gt;
ResultSet.getObject() method calls are not currently supported &lt;br/&gt;
for BLOB and CLOB.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
